G-CHAT-A2-POLISH — coherence gate (measured, not a SHA). 2026-06-19.
Engine: tools/sp_daemon {routes.rs, sampler.rs, tokenizer.rs}. Daemon: gemma4-12b-b1, run_console env
(SP_DAEMON_BACKEND=cuda, SP_DAEMON_KVDECODE=1, SP_CUDA_DECODE_INT8=1), ring DISARMED. Real 12B, :3000.

WHAT WAS BUILT
  (1) Full control-token suppression, id-agnostic. tokenizer.rs suppress_token_ids() now matches
      every pipe-wrapped control marker (decoded bytes start '<', end '>', contain '|') — 19 ids on
      the b1 vocab: <|turn> <turn|> <image|> <audio|> <|image> <|audio> <|image|> <|audio|> <|video|>
      <|tool> <tool|> <|tool_call> <tool_call|> <|tool_response> <tool_response|> <|"|> <|think|>
      <|channel> <channel|> — plus named structural specials <pad> <bos> <unk> <mask> and the
      <unusedN> reserve (exact match). <eos> deliberately excluded (eos_ids owns it). ZERO false
      positives on the b1 vocab (<div>/<html> survive: no pipe; |< |</ survive: don't start '<').
      Applied on BOTH the sampled and the greedy (temp=0) path so greedy is clean too.
  (2) raw_logits opt-out. ChatRequest.raw_logits (default false). true => sampler built with EMPTY
      suppress set => raw un-suppressed logits drive selection = the byte-exact/B1 determinism null
      floor. Default false => clean suppressed chat.
  (3) Turn-stop heuristic. This artifact has NO <end_of_turn> token; turn markers are <|turn>(105)/
      <turn|>(106). tokenizer.turn_stop_ids() returns those ids (id-agnostic); both decode loops treat
      them as EOS-equivalent (stop before the marker reaches the stream). default_stops() also extended
      with structural new-turn stop-strings (<start_of_turn>, <|turn>, <turn|>, "\n\nQuestion:",
      "\nUser:", "\n\nUser", "\nQuestion:") as a conservative belt-and-braces backstop.

UNIT TESTS (cargo test --release --features wire_cuda_backend, bin sp-daemon): 12 passed; 0 failed.
  new: sampler::suppress_applies_on_greedy_path, sampler::raw_logits_empty_suppress_is_old_argmax,
       tokenizer::a2_polish_tests::{suppresses_pipe_control_markers, suppresses_named_specials_and_reserve,
       does_not_suppress_text_or_eos}.

